  "title": "SENIOR QS/QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To prepare documents and submuissions for tendering new projects.</li>\n  <li>study contract documents, perform measurements and prepare Bill of Quantities;</li>\n  <li>To assist in contract administration, prepare progress claim(s) and liaise with the Client’s representative on claims and variation costs;</li>\n  <li>Call quotations, compare prices and prepare bill of quantities to arrive at the tender pricing;</li>\n  <li>To review and verify the Subcontractor’s / Supplier’s claims and prepare payment certificates</li>\n  <li>To attend site meeting and progress claim meeting;</li>\n  <li>Upon completion of each project, to monitor the respective project during the defect’s liability period;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Quantity Surveying or equivalent qualifications</li>\n  <li>Preferably at least 3 years of relevant working experience in Civil Engineering</li>\n  <li>Reliable with good communication and interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>Good technical and contractual knowledge with high integrity and work ethic</li>\n  <li>An independent and effective team player, collaborating on multi-projects of various stages, ensuring deliverables within set time &amp; expectations.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
